deck: Sacha Borisich was born in Chicago and now lives in Los Angeles. She is best known for illustrating Zuda webcomic Black Cherry Bombshells.
name: Sacha Borisich

deck: John Dallaire is a commercial illustrator and graphic designer, and the art director of sci-fi fan site pinkraygun.com. He has worked on a number of indie comics, including webcomic Black Cherry Bombshells.
name: John Dallaire

deck: Loren Meyer is an American illustrator. His most successful work is Zuda webcomic Blood Hunter, which he also wrote.
name: Loren Meyer

description: Zechary "Zech" Gray was born and raised in Miami Florida. He pursued a life as a comic book artist since he picked up his first comic book the X-MEN by then artist Marc Silvestri. In his early career he met Georges Jeanty who he credits to this day as his first mentor. Over the years he took a career switch as he joined the U.S. ARMY until 2008 where he suffered from injuries from an explosion. In 2010 after healing and falling back in love with drawing he was introduced to ANTARCTIC PRESS where he met Fred Perry, David Hutchison, Wes Hartman, Brian Denham and a host of other artists that took him into their fold. He is a huge admire of Jim Lee, Travis Charest, Art Adams, J Scott Campell, Greg Capullo.
name: Zechary Gray

description: Linda Sejic is a Croatian colorist and digital artist who has worked for comic companies like Dynamite, Top Cow and Zenescope. She is also the wife of fellow artist Stjepan Sejic.
name: Linda Luksic Šejić

deck: Sean Carolan is a comic book writer for DC Comics.  He has worked on Cartoon Network Block Party, Dexter's Laboratory, Hi Hi Puffy Amiyumi, The Powerpuff Girls, and Scooby-Doo.
name: Sean Carolan

deck: Reginald Thomas Maitland Scott was a Canadian fiction writer and the creator of Secret Service Smith. He also wrote the first two "The Spider" novels.
name: R.T.M. Scott

deck: Norvell Wordsworth Page was an American pulp fiction writer best known for his extensive work on The Spider. Page has also written stories for The Shadow and The Phantom.
name: Norvell W. Page

deck: Walter Martin Baumhofer was an American illustrator known for his cover art on pulp magazines.
name: Walter M. Baumhofer

deck: Legendary Spanish horror star. Creator of Waldemar Daninsky.
name: Paul Naschy

name: Jaime Salangsang

name: Sebastian Cichon

deck: Sarah Perryman is a colorist and digital painter who has worked for Image and Zenescope.
name: Sarah Perryman

deck: Stuart Brown is a colorist for Zenescope.
name: Stuart Brown

deck: Noval N. Hernawan is an artist who has drawn for Dynamite Entertainment, Marvel, and Zenescope.
